The paper proposes a new approach for fixed-complexity LLL reductions, which is a problem in lattice-based cryptography. This problem is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS) as it involves finding a basis for a lattice with certain properties. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the proposed approach, which is relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper evaluates the approach using simulations, which involves analyzing the error rate of the output, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the approach in terms of CPU time, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
